.TH ARACHNA 1 "2026-06-06" "arachna 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
arachna — context collector for AI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B arachna
[\fB\-\-profile\fR \fIname\fR]
[\fB\-\-all\fR]
[\fB\-\-snapshot\fR \fIcommand\fR]
[\fB\-\-diff\fR]
[\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
arachna collects project files into token-limited chunks ready to be
sent to an AI. It understands tokens (not lines) and splits output
smartly so nothing gets cut in the middle.
.PP
Supports multiple profiles for different AI tasks (code, tests, docs,
git history), incremental collection with smart caching, content-
addressable snapshots with diffs, and query-based file filtering.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Collection
.TP
\fB\-\-init\fR
Interactive setup wizard. Creates \fI.arachna.json\fR.
.TP
\fB\-\-init \-\-defaults\fR
Auto-detect project type and create config.
.TP
\fB\-\-init \-\-preset\fR \fIname\fR
Use specific preset (godot, unity, docker, etc.).
.TP
\fB\-\-all\fR
Collect all profiles.
.TP
\fB\-\-profile\fR \fIname\fR
Collect specific profile (code, tests, docs, git).
.TP
\fB\-\-list\fR
Show available profiles.
.TP
\fB\-\-clean\fR
Remove all collected files.
.SS Watch (Snapshots and Diffs)
.TP
\fB\-\-snapshot\fR
Show usage hint.
.TP
\fB\-\-snapshot list\fR
List all snapshots.
.TP
\fB\-\-snapshot create \-\-profile\fR \fIname\fR \fB\-\-name\fR \fIid\fR
Create a named snapshot.
.TP
\fB\-\-snapshot update\fR \fIid\fR
Update an existing snapshot with current state.
.TP
\fB\-\-snapshot delete\fR \fIid\fR
Delete a snapshot.
.TP
\fB\-\-snapshot info\fR \fIid\fR
Show snapshot details.
.TP
\fB\-\-snapshot rename\fR \fIold\fR \fInew\fR
Rename a snapshot.
.TP
\fB\-\-diff\fR
Diff from single snapshot (auto-select).
.TP
\fB\-\-diff \-\-from\fR \fIid\fR
Diff from specific snapshot.
.TP
\fB\-\-diff \-\-from\fR \fIA\fR \fB\-\-to\fR \fIB\fR
Cross-snapshot diff between two snapshots.
.TP
\fB\-\-diff \-\-stat\fR
Show statistics only (no content).
.TP
\fB\-\-diff \-\-flat\fR
Flat output without grouping (backward compatible).
.TP
\fB\-\-diff \-\-mode structural\fR
Structural diff — understands code blocks, not just lines.
.SS Store
.TP
\fB\-\-store stats\fR
Show store statistics (snapshots, objects, dedup).
.TP
\fB\-\-store gc\fR
Garbage collect unreferenced objects.
.SS Diagnostics
.TP
\fB\-\-validate\fR
Check config for errors.
.TP
\fB\-\-doctor\fR
Run full diagnostic.
.TP
\fB\-\-install\-hook\fR
Install post-commit git hook.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-output\-dir\fR \fIpath\fR
Output directory (default: arachna_context/).
.TP
\fB\-\-verbose\fR
Show skipped files.
.TP
\fB\-\-compress\fR
Compress whitespace to save tokens.
.TP
\fB\-\-incremental\fR
Only collect changed files.
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fIxml|json\fR
Output format (default: markdown).
.TP
\fB\-\-merge\fR
Append to existing output instead of replacing.
.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Preview without writing files.
.TP
\fB\-\-query\fR \fItext\fR
Filter files by query (keyword scoring + import chain).
.TP
\fB\-\-mode\fR \fIfull|headers|repo\-map\fR
Collection mode (default: full).
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI.arachna.json\fR
Project configuration (profiles, output directory, tokenizer).
.TP
\fIarachna_context/\fR
Default output directory for collected context.
.TP
\fI.arachna/store/\fR
Content-addressable store for snapshots (never committed).
.TP
\fI.arachna_cache.json\fR
Incremental mode cache (mtime_ns + size + SHA256).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
arachna uses no environment variables. All configuration is in
\fI.arachna.json\fR.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Success.
.TP
1
Error (invalid config, missing profile, etc.).
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Quick start:
.nf
    cd my\-project
    arachna \-\-init
    arachna \-\-all
.fi
.PP
Agent workflow with snapshots:
.nf
    arachna \-\-snapshot create \-\-profile code \-\-name baseline
    # ... AI makes changes ...
    arachna \-\-diff \-\-from baseline
.fi
.PP
Programmatic API (Python):
.nf
    from arachna import watch
    sid = watch.create_snapshot(profile="full", name="baseline")
    diff = watch.compute_diff(snapshot_id="baseline", mode="structural")
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
Full documentation: \fIhttps://github.com/dead\-duke/arachna\fR
